<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="600" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,548,1042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="600">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,299,766,790]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="600" reason="1">Remark.</emphasis>
In the species’ original description, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson, G. F." box="[684,864,766,790]" pageId="4" pageNumber="600" pagination="1 - 590" refId="ref3098" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1900) Catalogue of the Arctiadae (Nolinae, Lithosianae) in the British Museum. Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, 2, 1 - 590." type="journal article" year="1900">Hampson (1900)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned two specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1211,1346,766,790]" name="South Africa" pageId="4" pageNumber="600">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and one from 
<collectingCountry box="[211,340,802,826]" name="Madagascar" pageId="4" pageNumber="600">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
as well. The author of this present paper could not locate the Madagascan specimen in the NHMUK collection, but most probably it belongs to another, externally similar species (e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="(Toulgoet, 1954))" baseAuthorityName="Toulgoet" baseAuthorityYear="1954" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Parexilisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctoides">
<emphasis box="[1058,1318,838,862]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="600">Parexilisia bipunctoides</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Toulgoet, H. de" pageId="4" pageNumber="600" pagination="345 - 359" refId="ref3171" refString="Toulgoet, H. de (1954) Description d'Arctiidae nouveaux de Madagascar (Lep.). Memoires de l'Institut scientifique de Madagascar, Serie E, 4, 345 - 359. [in French]" type="journal article" year="1954">Toulgoët, 1954</bibRefCitation>
))
</taxonomicName>
. The second South African 
<typeStatus box="[527,610,874,898]" pageId="4" pageNumber="600">syntype</typeStatus>
specimen mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson, G. F." box="[882,1064,874,898]" pageId="4" pageNumber="600" pagination="1 - 590" refId="ref3098" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1900) Catalogue of the Arctiadae (Nolinae, Lithosianae) in the British Museum. Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, 2, 1 - 590." type="journal article" year="1900">Hampson (1900)</bibRefCitation>
as “Ab. 1.” and described later as ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1900" box="[160,366,910,934]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Philenora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipuncta">
<emphasis box="[160,366,910,934]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="600">Philenora bipuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ab. 
<emphasis box="[410,522,910,933]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="600">prominens</emphasis>
Strand, 1922’ is not conspecific to the first male 
<typeStatus box="[1041,1127,910,934]" pageId="4" pageNumber="600">syntype</typeStatus>
. In order to preserve stability of nomenclature, the specimen from Cape deposited in the NHMUK collection and labeled as “Type” is designated here as 
<typeStatus box="[180,281,982,1006]" pageId="4" pageNumber="600">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
